# Vuexy UI source of truth

When adding or changing UI in this app:

1. **Prefer existing Vuexy pieces** from the sibling full template: `../full-version` (same parent folder as this `starter-kit`). Do **not** build bespoke UI primitives (buttons, cards, dialogs, layout chrome, form patterns, tables, charts wrappers, etc.) when the full template already provides an equivalent.

2. **How to reuse**
   - Copy the relevant files from `full-version` into this project (typically under `src/components`, `src/views`, `src/libs`, routes under `src/app`, and types/utils as needed).
   - Add npm dependencies from `full-version/package.json` only for features you actually port.
   - Keep imports consistent with existing path aliases (`@components/*`, `@core/*`, `@layouts/*`, `@menu/*`, etc.).

3. **Core folders** (`src/@core`, `src/@layouts`, `src/@menu`): do not edit in place. To customize, follow Vuexy’s pattern—copy into `src/components` (or project-specific folders) and change imports—per official “Customizing our components” guidance.

4. **MUI**: use MUI and the template’s wrappers/overrides; for standard MUI usage, align with patterns already used in `full-version`.

This rule exists so the product stays visually and structurally aligned with Vuexy and avoids duplicate, one-off components.
